# Roadmap Sync

When work follows `ROADMAP.md`, treat it as a living checklist — not a static doc.

## When to update

- **Completed step** → change `- [ ]` to `- [x]` for that item
- **Scope change** → add, remove, or rewrite affected steps so the roadmap stays accurate
- **New phase or decision** → document it in the roadmap before finishing the turn
- **Status section** → update "Current status" and "Next step" at the bottom

## What to update

| Change | Roadmap action |
|--------|----------------|
| Finished a checklist item | Mark it done |
| Partial progress on a step | Add sub-bullets or split the step; mark only what is done |
| Blocked or deferred work | Note the blocker and adjust "Next step" |
| Architecture decision | Add under "Open decisions" or the relevant phase |

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] Every roadmap item addressed this session is reflected in `ROADMAP.md`
- [ ] "Current status" and "Next step" match reality
- [ ] No completed work left with unchecked boxes

If the session did not touch roadmap-tracked work, no update is required.
